Question 2: "What is ISBN_text.pdf?"
ISBN = a book's unique ID number (like an Aadhaar number but for books). Every book in the world has one — it's 13 digits.

The file naming rule they want is:

9780134685991_text.pdf
  ─────────────  ────  ───
       │          │     │
       │          │     └── File format (pdf or png)
       │          │
       │          └── Literally the word "text" (just a label)
       │
       └── The ISBN number (identifies WHICH book this is)
WHY this naming matters:
Your script reads the filename to know which book it's dealing with:

python
filename = "9780134685991_text.pdf"
isbn = filename.split("_")[0]    # → "9780134685991"
# Now you can look up:
# - Who is the author of book 9780134685991? → "Raj Jain"
# - What is their email? → "raj@email.com"
# - Has this book been submitted before? → Check Airtable
Without the ISBN in the filename, your system wouldn't know whose book cover it's analyzing and who to email the results to.

